  "prompt": "What are some publicly listed solar companies in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, there are several publicly listed solar companies in India that are involved in the manufacturing, installation, and maintenance of solar energy products and solutions. Here are some prominent ones:\n\n1. **Tata Power Solar Systems Limited**: A subsidiary of Tata Power, this company is one of the largest solar manufacturers in India and is involved in the production of solar panels and modules, as well as EPC (Engineering, Procurement, and Construction) services for solar power projects.\n\n2. **Adani Green Energy Limited (AGEL)**: A part of the Adani Group, AGEL is one of the largest renewable energy companies in India, focusing on solar and wind energy generation.\n\n3. **Azure Power Global Limited**: An independent solar power producer, Azure Power develops, builds, owns, and operates solar energy plants across India.\n\n4. **Waaree Energies Ltd**: One of India\u2019s largest manufacturers of solar panels, Waaree Energies is involved in the production of solar PV modules and also provides EPC services, solar water pumps, and rooftop solar installations.\n\n5. **Suzlon Energy Limited**: Although primarily known for wind energy, Suzlon also has a significant presence in the solar energy sector, providing solar power solutions and services.\n\n6. **JinkoSolar Holding Co., Ltd.**: While it is a global company headquartered in China, JinkoSolar has a significant presence in India and is one of the largest and most innovative solar module manufacturers in the world.\n\n7. **First Solar, Inc.**: Another global company with operations in India, First Solar is known for its advanced thin-film photovoltaic modules and comprehensive utility-scale PV power solutions.\n\n8. **Vikram Solar Limited**: One of the leading module manufacturers and solar EPC solution providers in India, Vikram Solar is known for its high-quality solar products and projects.\n\n9. **Loom Solar Pvt. Ltd.**: Specializing in mono PERC solar panels, Loom Solar has gained a reputation for high-efficiency solar products and is expanding its presence across India.\n\n10. **Renew Power (ReNew Energy Global Plc)**: One of the largest renewable energy IPPs (Independent Power Producers) in India, Renew Power has a significant portfolio of solar and wind energy projects.\n\nThese companies are listed on various stock exchanges in India and globally, and they play a crucial role in the development and deployment of solar energy across the country. Always check the latest financial reports and market conditions before making investment decisions, as the renewable energy sector can be highly dynamic.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
